main event: A red square object, 1-2 feet in diameter, moved across the sky and disappeared from view after being observed for 50 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for only 50 seconds., The object was initially seen moving south to west., It was observed with binoculars for 10 seconds., The report suggests that the object could be a meteor, based on its flight duration and distance., The object expanded before fading from view.
witness description: Civilian age 14 years from Racine, Wisconsin
